<div class="cordyceps-container">
    <h1 class="cordyceps-title">Anti-cancer Properties</h1>

    <p class="cordyceps-text">A study in <strong>Frontiers in Oncology (2024)</strong> identified that cordycepin, an active compound in 
        <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong>, inhibits the proliferation of cancer cells, induces apoptosis (programmed cell death), and 
        reduces metastasis in various cancer types.</p>

    <div class="section_image_div">
        <img class="section_image" src="content/section4_image.png" alt="Anti-cancer Properties">  
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What was the study about?</h2>
        <p class="cordyceps-text">This study focused on cordycepin, a natural compound found in the medicinal mushroom <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong>, 
            and its ability to fight cancer. The researchers wanted to understand how cordycepin works to stop cancer cells from 
            growing and spreading.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What did the researchers do?</h2>
        <ul class="cordyceps-list">
            <li>They studied cordycepin's effects on different types of cancer cells in the lab.</li>
            <li>They looked at how cordycepin caused cancer cells to die through a process called apoptosis 
                (a natural and controlled way for damaged or harmful cells to self-destruct).</li>
            <li>They also analyzed whether cordycepin affected healthy cells.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What did they find?</h2>
        <ul class="cordyceps-list">
            <li><strong>Kills Cancer Cells:</strong> Cordycepin specifically targeted cancer cells, forcing them to go through apoptosis.</li>
            <li><strong>Blocks Cancer Spread:</strong> It stopped cancer cells from growing and spreading by interfering with their DNA and protein production.</li>
            <li><strong>Safe for Healthy Cells:</strong> Unlike many traditional cancer treatments, cordycepin did not significantly harm healthy cells, making it a promising alternative therapy.</li>
            <li><strong>Works with Existing Treatments:</strong> Cordycepin enhanced the effects of other cancer treatments like chemotherapy, suggesting it could be used alongside them for better results.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">Why is this important?</h2>
        <p class="cordyceps-text">Cancer is one of the leading causes of death worldwide, and many treatments have harmful side effects. 
            Cordycepin offers a natural, targeted, and less toxic way to treat cancer. Its ability to selectively kill cancer cells while 
            sparing healthy ones makes it a promising candidate for future therapies.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cordyceps-section">
        <h2 class="cordyceps-heading">What does this mean for you?</h2>
        <p class="cordyceps-text">Cordycepin from <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong> shows potential as a natural anticancer treatment. 
            While the results are exciting, this is still early research done mostly in labs. More clinical trials on humans are needed 
            to confirm its safety and effectiveness. If you're considering supplements or treatments involving <strong>Cordyceps militaris</strong>, 
            consult a healthcare professional first.</p>
    </div>

